            "id": "DJN_DN20260216002952:0",
            "title": "Australia Shares Poised to Nudge Higher at Open — Market Talk",
            "description": "<div class=\"body-KX2tCBZq body-pIO_GYwT content-pIO_GYwT\"><div class=\"symbolsContainer-cBh_FN2P logosContainer-cwMMKgmm\" data-no-swipe=\"true\"></div><div><span><p class=\"\"><span>Australian equities are poised to nudge higher at the open amid earnings reports from companies including BHP, Challenger and Seek. Local stock futures are up by 0.3% ahead of Tuesday's session, suggesting the S&amp;P/ASX 200 will add to its week-opening 0.2% rise in early trade. A public holiday in the U.S. means the benchmark index has no lead from Wall Street to follow. Ahead of the open, wealth manager Challenger said it would buy back up to A$150 million in shares after a surge in 1H profit. Reliance Worldwide reported a 35% drop in 1H profit. Miner BHP and jobs advertiser Seek are among companies scheduled to report later Tuesday. (stuart.condie@wsj.com)</span></p></span></div></div>",
